    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Dissolve your<strong> vegetable stock mix </strong>in 750ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[975ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.4L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mozzarella-topped-tomato-risotto-with-basil-oil/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mozzarella-topped-tomato-risotto-with-basil-oil/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3 min until soft but not coloured</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mozzarella-topped-tomato-risotto-with-basil-oil/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> arborio rice</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the softened onion</p><p>Mix well to make sure the rice is evenly coated in the onion and oil</p><p>Add your <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> and stir continuously until the rice has absorbed most of the tomato juice</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mozzarella-topped-tomato-risotto-with-basil-oil/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock</strong> a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for 25-30 min or until all the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mozzarella-topped-tomato-risotto-with-basil-oil/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Grind the <strong>chopped basil</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> to form a paste</p><p>Add 3-4 tbsp <strong>olive oil </strong>or enough to loosen and mix well \u2013 this is your <strong>basil oil</strong></p><p>Tip: If you don't have a pestle & mortar, chop the basil leaves very finely and mix with salt and olive oil</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mozzarella-topped-tomato-risotto-with-basil-oil/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the risotto is nearly cooked, stir in your <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> and 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and cook for a further 2 min \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato risotto</strong></p><p>Season the <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>risotto</strong> with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Drain your <strong>mozzarella</strong>, then pat and squeeze as much liquid out as you can with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mozzarella-topped-tomato-risotto-with-basil-oil/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>risotto</strong> in a bowl</p><p>Tear the <strong>mozzarella</strong> in half<strong> </strong>and nestle into the tomato risotto so that it melts nicely</p><p>Drizzle the <strong>basil oil</strong> over the top</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
